title: Saif stabbing case: 1000-page chargesheet filed, forensic links knife to accused

description: Stock market today: BSE Sensex and Nifty50, the Indian equity benchmark indices, opened in red on Wednesday ahead of RBI’s monetary policy review. While BSE Sensex dipped over 350 points, Nifty50 was below 22,450.
title: Stock market today: BSE Sensex opens over 350 points down; Nifty50 below 22,450

description: Donald Trump's new "reciprocal" tariffs, now at 104% on Chinese goods, have triggered a global trade war, disrupting markets and sparking recession fears. This layered tariff approach, starting with duties related to fentanyl and escalating with retaliatory measures, has sent stock markets plummeting and is expected to raise consumer prices.
title: TOI explainer: The math behind Donald Trump’s 104% tariffs on China

description: A tragic fire at a nursing home in Hebei province, China, has claimed the lives of at least 20 people. The blaze erupted around 9:00 pm local time on Tuesday in Longhua County, approximately 180 kilometres from Beijing. While the fire has been brought under control, several elderly residents were evacuated to nearby hospitals for treatment.
title: 20 killed in fire at northern China nursing home, probe under way
5.0-magnitude quake strikes Taiwan, no immediate damage reported

description: Premier Li Qiang affirmed China's capacity to manage economic challenges amidst US tariffs, assuring Ursula von der Leyen of the nation's policy reserves and confidence in sustained growth. During their call, both leaders explored ways to stabilize the global economy following disruptions caused by US trade measures.
title: Chinese premier says Beijing has 'sufficient tools' to fight Trump's tariffs

description: Gurmeet Ram Rahim Singh, the controversial Dera Sacha Sauda chief convicted of rape, has been granted a 21-day furlough by the Haryana government. This temporary release follows a pattern of paroles and furloughs often coinciding with key election periods, raising concerns about potential political influence.
title: Convicted rapist Gurmeet Ram Rahim out of jail again, granted 21-day furlough

description: President Trump defends his tariff policy amidst market volatility and economic unease, asserting his commitment to American workers over Wall Street interests. Despite warnings from economists and pressure from business leaders, Trump shows no signs of backing down from his aggressive trade stance. This resolve sets the stage for continued clashes and potential economic challenges.
title: 'I'm President who stands up for Main Street, not Wall Street': Trump

description: Senior Congress leader and literary figure Kumari Ananthan passed away in Chennai at 93 due to age-related illness. He was a five-time Tamil Nadu Assembly member and a former Lok Sabha MP. His daughter, BJP leader Tamilisai Soundararajan, expressed deep sorrow, remembering his profound love for the Tamil language. Ananthan's body will be available for tributes at Soundararajan's Chennai residence.
title: Senior Congress leader Kumari Ananthan passes away at 93 in Chennai
Buy or sell: Stock recommendation by brokers for today

description: US Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth visited Panama. He promised collaboration to curb China's influence on the Panama Canal. Hegseth's visit marks growing US concerns about Chinese projects in the region. Former President Trump suggested military force to reclaim the canal. President Jose Raul Mulino supports US efforts. He pulled Panama out of China's Belt and Road Initiative.
title: Pentagon says US will help Panama take back canal from Chinese influence

description: Saif Ali Khan was attacked by a burglar at his Mumbai home, who entered his son Jeh's room. Saif was stabbed six times while protecting his son. After surgery and treatment, he has recovered and resumed work. Police have arrested Shariful Islam from Bangladesh and filed a 1000-page chargesheet including forensic evidence linking him to the crime.
title: Saif Ali Khan attack case: Mumbai police files 1000-page charge sheet

description: King Charles III and Queen Camilla are celebrating their 20th wedding anniversary with new portraits taken in Rome during their state visit to Italy.
title: 20 years of King Charles-Camilla's marriage: When Harry, William begged him not to remarry

description: India's mobile phone exports surged to over Rs 2 lakh crore in fiscal 2024-25, driven by Apple's iPhone, which accounted for Rs 1.5 lakh crore. The government aims to boost the electronics manufacturing ecosystem with a Rs 22,919 crore incentive scheme, targeting increased value addition and job creation in the sector.
title: Mobile phone exports top Rs 2L crore mark in FY25

description: Salman Khan's 'Sikandar' struggles at the box office, crossing ₹100 crore but failing to meet expectations due to its high ₹250 crore budget. The film opened strong at ₹26 crore but declined after Eid, with recent earnings dropping to ₹1.35 crore on Tuesday.
title: 'Sikandar' box office collection: Salman starrer sees all-time low on 2nd Tuesday

description: Former MLB pitcher Octavio Dotel was present at the Jet Set nightclub in Santo Domingo when its roof collapsed during a performance by singer Rubby Perez. Dotel was found under debris but survived. Tragically, the incident resulted in at least 13 fatalities and numerous injuries, with 93 ambulance transfers reported as rescue efforts continue.
title: Ex MLB pitcher Dotel rescued after nightclub roof collapses in Dominican Republic

description: Olivier Rioux, the 7'9" Canadian redshirt freshman, is generating excitement at the University of Florida despite not yet playing. Recognized by Guinness World Records, Rioux's towering presence and training at IMG Academy have made him a fan favorite. As the Gators celebrate their national championship, anticipation builds for Rioux's debut and potential impact on college basketball and beyond.
title: Florida Gators wins it all, yet 7’9” freshman Olivier Rioux becomes unexpected hero

description: Suchana Seth, accused of murdering her son in Goa, has been further charged with assaulting a female police constable in Colvale Central Jail. The incident occurred when Seth allegedly took a register without permission and then physically attacked the officer, causing injuries.
title: Bengaluru CEO, under trial for son’s murder, assaults lady constable in jail

description: A tragic incident occurred in Santo Domingo. The Jet Set nightclub's roof collapsed during a merengue concert. Sixty-six people died and over 160 sustained injuries. Rescue teams are searching for more survivors. Octavio Dotel and Tony Blanco, former baseball players, are among the dead. Nelsy Cruz, a governor, also died. The cause of the collapse is under investigation.
title: Dominican nightclub roof collapses during concert, killing 66: What we know so far

description: Despite RBI's repo rate cuts, deposit rates remain high, impacting banks' cost of funds. While home loan borrowers benefit, depositors see limited gains due to investor shifts and liquidity pressures. Experts anticipate further repo rate cuts, but transmission to deposit rates will be gradual, influenced by banks' liquidity coverage and policy stance.
title: RBI set for rate cut, banks’ cost of funds may not drop

description: A shooting in Spotsylvania County, Virginia, left three people dead and three others injured on Tuesday evening. The incident occurred outside a townhouse complex on Olde Greenwich Circle, prompting a large-scale investigation by law enforcement. Authorities are actively searching for suspects, and the motive behind the shooting remains unclear as the investigation continues.
title: Three dead, three injured in Virginia shooting; suspect on the run

description: President Trump defended his tariff policies, claiming billions in revenue while signing orders to boost the coal industry. However, US stocks tumbled amid trade war uncertainty, with the S&P 500 reversing gains. Trump's coal-focused executive orders aim to revitalize the sector, facing criticism for prioritizing a polluting energy source.
title: Trump claims $2bn daily from ‘explosive’ tariffs, hours before they take effect

description: A 1988 interview featuring Donald Trump on The Oprah Winfrey Show has resurfaced, revealing his long-held views on international trade. In the interview, Trump expressed frustration with allies like Japan and Kuwait, accusing them of exploiting the United States.
title: When 'angry' Trump gave 'tariff warning' to Oprah Winfrey in 1988 interview
